<blockquote>"<em><strong>Here comes the story of the Hurricane
The man the authorities came to blame<strong></em>"
~ Bob Dylan</blockquote>While this is not the same story that Dylan sang about, Michael Lewis offers unique insights into the hurricane life of Sam Bankman-Fried, Boy Billionaire, Crypto Criminal.

Five Business Lessons Learned:

1. When you have no skill in management—and have no interest in learning—hire someone who is both experienced and capable to lead the operation.

2. When you start up two companies, don't commingle funds between them.

3. When your companies feature millions of dollars of transactions, hire a CFO to manage the process.

4. When your attorneys advise you to keep your mouth shut, keep your mouth shut.

5. Don't pay Tom Brady $55 million for approximately 60 hours of promotional work, EVER!
